name: Highest Quality Meat
description:
The best of four tiers of meat, this meat comes from the largest creatures in the game, such as Bears, Wolves, and Alligators
Cooking this meat with Mint, Oregano, or Fresh Thyme to get an additional boost to either health, stamina, or dead eye respectively.

name: High Quality Meat
description: High Quality Meat includes Exotic Bird Meat (Parrots, Pelicans), Mature Venison (Deer), Game Meat (Rabbits, Ducks), Succulent Fish (Salmon, Trout), Prime Beef (Cows, Bison), Tender Pork Loin (Javelina, Pigs)

name: Good Quality Meat
description: Good quality meat includes Plump Bird Meat (Turkey, Chicken, Geese), Crustacean Meat (Shellfish), Gristly Mutton (Sheep, Goats), Flaky Fish (Perch, Bass)

name: Low Quality Meat
description: Low Quality Meat includes Gritty Fish (Bluegill, etc), Gamey Birds (Small Birds), Stringy Meat (Rats, etc.), Herptile Meat (Reptiles)

name: Bird Feather
description:
Each bird in the game has its own feather, some more valuable than others. The most valuable feathers are the Spoonbill Plumes, Condor Feathers, Heron Plumes, and Egret Feathers.
Different variants of Arthur's Hat can be purchased at the trapper using different types of bird feathers.

name: Flight Feather
description: Flight feathers are harvested from flying birds, and are used in crafting recipes for Improved, Fire, Poison, and Small Game Arrows. They can also be sold for $0.15 each.

name: Alligator Skin
description: You can use the Alligator skin to craft the Alligator saddle at the trapper.
